Considine was also active as an author, especially as a collaborator with famous persons writing their autobiographies. His books include
Thirty Seconds Over Tokyo (with Capt. Ted Lawson);
Gen. Wainwright's Story (with Gen. Jonathan Wainwright);
The Babe Ruth Story (with Babe Ruth);
Men Against Fire,
The Men Who Robbed Brink's. and
The Remarkable Life of Dr. Armand Hammer. He also wrote for the movies, including
The Babe Ruth Story for Allied Artists and
The Beginning or the End (about the development of the first atomic bomb) for MGM.
